{
  "prompt": "Implement a fun web game called \"Park Perfection\" where players strategically place and manage park amenities to create the perfect neighborhood space while avoiding obstacles.\n\nFeatures:\n- Create a fixed-size 2D grid representing an empty park space, with a grass-textured background created using CSS patterns.\n- Display a selection of park amenities (benches, trees, playground equipment, fountains) represented by simple geometric shapes with distinct colors.\n- Show a \"currently selected\" amenity indicator in the top-left corner.\n- Implement a hover effect that shows a preview of where the selected amenity will be placed.\n- Create wandering NPCs (represented by small circles) that move randomly across the park space.\n- NPCs should gravitate towards placed amenities, increasing a \"satisfaction score\" when they interact with them.\n- Display a \"satisfaction meter\" that fills based on NPCs interacting with amenities.\n- Add \"problem spots\" that randomly appear on the grid (represented by red squares), which decrease the satisfaction meter if not addressed quickly.\n- Implement a budget system that starts at 1000 points and decreases with each placed amenity (different amenities cost different amounts).\n- Show the current budget prominently at the top of the screen.\n- Create visual feedback when placing amenities (brief sparkle effect) or when removing problem spots (puff of smoke).\n- Display a \"Game Over\" screen when either the budget reaches zero or the satisfaction meter empties completely.\n- Generate a final score based on the number of happy NPCs and remaining budget.\n- Include a \"Best Score\" display that updates when beaten.\n\nUser Actions:\n1. Use number keys 1-4 to select different park amenities, then click on the grid to place them (if budget allows).\n2. Right-click on problem spots to remove them (costs a small amount of budget).\nNote:\n- Your output should be implemented in JavaScript with HTML and CSS.\n- Ensure that the output has both index.js and index.html files",
